Create a Catalog Item

Catalog items are pieces of metadata that represent items available in the service catalog. Customers use finished catalog items to generate catalog requests, making it vital that you structure catalog items to get the information you require to answer those requests.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions

Primary and secondary catalog categories can have up to 100 items. Your service catalog can have up to 1,000 catalog items.

To create a catalog item, click New Catalog Item.
In Item Details, enter a name and description, and upload an optional image.
In Fulfillment Configuration, complete these steps:
Select Fulfillment to add an underlying fulfillment for your catalog item.
View and define the inputs assigned to that fulfillment.
If any inputs require customer input, change how that input is posed as a question to the customer.

In Categorization, select a category for your catalog item.
Internal Access: Select who can see the catalog item in the catalog. Turn off Allow Access for All Users to restrict users.
External Access: Select who can see the catalog item in the catalog. If Guest Visibility is on, you canâ€™t use eligibility rules.

To set eligibility rules, turn off Allow customers to access catalog items after authentication. Apply Rules, then select the eligibility rules you want to assign to this catalog item.
Save your work.

Your catalog item is saved in draft state.
To activate your catalog item, click Activate.

You can edit, clone, and delete catalog items. Deleting a catalog item clears up space in its associated catalog categories and hides it from Service Catalog users.

Mark a Catalog Item as Featured

Catalog items marked as Featured are displayed prominently in Service Catalog, helping your customers quickly find the services they use the most.
Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions
On the Service Catalog Builder landing page, locate the item. Click Add to Featured.
title: Service Cloud - Create and Manage Catalog Items
